50|$|Garden {{lighting}} can be {{an important}} aspect of garden design. In most cases, various types of lighting techniques may be classified and defined by heights: <b>safety</b> <b>lighting,</b> uplighting, and downlighting. <b>Safety</b> <b>lighting</b> is the most practical application. However, {{it is more important to}} determine the type of lamps and fittings needed to create the desired effects. Light regulates three major plant processes: photosynthesis, phototropism, and photoperiodism.|$|R
