50|$|Typically, <b>safety</b> <b>light</b> {{curtains}} {{are connected}} to a safety relay which will remove motive power from the hazard {{in the event that}} an object is detected. Safety relays can be provided with muting functionality which enables the temporary disabling of the safety function to allow objects to pass through the <b>safety</b> <b>light</b> curtains without tripping the safety relay. This is particularly useful for machinery which has some semi-automatic procedures.|$|E
